<td sourcefile="Solutions/factoring-setup.md" sourcestartlinenumber="24"><strong sourcefile="Solutions/factoring-setup.md" sourcestartlinenumber="24">Chart of Accounts</strong></td>
<td sourcefile="Solutions/factoring-setup.md" sourcestartlinenumber="24">Chart of Accounts It is necessary to open financial accounts for tracking receivables, cost and revenue accounts for factoring re-accounting; if they no longer exist.</td>
</tr>
<tr sourcefile="Solutions/factoring-setup.md" sourcestartlinenumber="25">
<td sourcefile="Solutions/factoring-setup.md" sourcestartlinenumber="25"><strong sourcefile="Solutions/factoring-setup.md" sourcestartlinenumber="25">Factoring group account</strong></td>
<td sourcefile="Solutions/factoring-setup.md" sourcestartlinenumber="25">hrough the Customer group account, it is necessary to create a new factoring group account, which will be used for factoring accounting. <img src="media/faktoring_setup_groupes.png" sourcefile="Solutions/factoring-setup.md" sourcestartlinenumber="25" alt="Factoring groups"></td>
</tr>
